#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:6
msgid "Mixxx Controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:8
msgid ""
"Nearly every knob, button, or fader you see in Mixxx's interface is "
"controllable via Mixxx's \"control\" system. The control system allows "
"skins, :term:`MIDI` controllers, :term:`HID` controllers and keyboards to "
"control Mixxx via a single interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:13
msgid ""
"A control is identified by a \"group\" (which is used for grouping "
"associated controls) and a \"key\" (the name of the individual control)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:16
msgid ""
"For example, the volume fader for Deck 1 is identified by the group "
":mixxx:cogroupref:`[Channel1] <[ChannelN]>` and key :mixxx:coref:`volume "
"<[Channel1],volume>`. Similarly, the volume fader for Sampler 1 is "
"identified by the group :mixxx:cogroupref:`[Sampler1] <[SamplerN]>` and key "
":mixxx:coref:`volume <[Sampler1],volume>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:21
msgid ""
"The group is used to collect all the controls that affect one component of "
"Mixxx into one collection. Some groups have a high overlap of controls in "
"common (e.g. samplers, decks, and the preview deck all share the same "
"control keys)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:26
msgid ""
"In addition to controlling Mixxx, the control system can be used to inspect "
"Mixxx's state. For example, the sample rate of the track loaded in Deck 1 "
"can be accessed via the :mixxx:coref:`[Channel1],track_samplerate` control. "
"You can read the :mixxx:coref:`[Channel3],play` control to determine whether"
" Deck 3 is playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:32
msgid ""
"The default value range is 0.0 to 1.0, unless otherwise noted. Binary means "
"that it is either 'ON' (non-zero) or 'OFF' (zero)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:35
msgid "Discovering Controls used in Skins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:37
msgid ""
"You can view the control connected to any part of a skin by running Mixxx "
"with the ``--developer`` command line option and hovering your mouse cursor "
"over part of the skin. If no tooltip appears, enable tooltips for the "
"Library and Skin in :menuselection:`Options --> Preferences --> Interface`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:42
msgid "Changing any control from the GUI in Developer Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:44
msgid ""
"When running Mixxx in Developer Mode (with the ``--developer`` command line "
"option), you can view and manually set the state of any control in Mixxx by "
"going to :menuselection:`Developer --> Developer Tools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:48
msgid "Simplify mapping of more complex behaviour"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:50
msgid ""
"While simple mappings with just a few buttons, knobs and LEDs can easily be "
"created with the MIDI Wizard and some basic scripting, implementing more "
"complex behaviour like switching deck layers or pad grid modes can be "
"tedious and error-prone. For these cases you can use Mixxx' `Comonents-JS "
"library <https://github.com/mixxxdj/mixxx/wiki/Components-JS>`_ which "
"provides building blocks for single controls as well as entire containers "
"like decks and effect units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/appendix/mixxx_controls.rst:57
msgid "See :ref:`controlindex` for a full list."
msgstr ""

